ivardefs.name: author_
ivardefs.desc: Identifies who is the author of the manifest. Manifest author is not necessarly the author of the references included.

ivardefs.name: content_
ivardefs.desc: The list of Resources that consist of the parts of this manifest.

ivardefs.name: created
ivardefs.desc: When the document manifest was created for submission to the server (not necessarily the same thing as the actual resource last modified time, since it may be modified, replicated, etc.).

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: Human-readable description of the source document. This is sometimes known as the "title".

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: Other identifiers associated with the document manifest, including version independent  identifiers.

ivardefs.name: masterIdentifier
ivardefs.desc: A single identifier that uniquely identifies this manifest. Principally used to refer to the manifest in non-FHIR contexts.

ivardefs.name: recipient_
ivardefs.desc: A patient, practitioner, or organization for which this set of documents is intended.

ivardefs.name: related_
ivardefs.desc: Related identifiers or resources associated with the DocumentManifest.

ivardefs.name: source
ivardefs.desc: Identifies the source system, application, or software that produced the document manifest.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of this document manifest.

ivardefs.name: subject
ivardefs.desc: Who or what the set of documents is about. The documents can be about a person, (patient or healthcare practitioner), a device (i.e. machine) or even a group of subjects (such as a document about a herd of farm animals, or a set of patients that share a c

ivardefs.name: type
ivardefs.desc: The code specifying the type of clinical activity that resulted in placing the associated content into the DocumentManifest.

properties.desc: A collection of documents compiled for a purpose together with metadata that applies to the collection.
